The paper deals with fine-grained image classification, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed approach involves attention mechanisms and spatial constraints, which are common techniques in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also evaluates its approach on four datasets, which are commonly used in multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) research.
